      "content": "Moving clockwise on the circle of fifths means you are moving up a perfect fifth, which increases the number of sharps or flats by one. Conversely, moving counter-clockwise means you are moving down a perfect fifth, which decreases the number of sharps or flats by one. This predictable pattern is why the circle is so useful for navigating key signatures!",
      "source": "target",
